Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Engineer II – Platform Engineering position with Infinite Campus. I bring over three years of professional experience in DevOps, platform engineering, and cloud infrastructure, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade platform infrastructure that directly reflects the enterprise-level DevOps and AWS expertise this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected scalable platform infrastructure for 1000+ API endpoints with automated deployment pipelines and AWS networking (VPC, security groups), ensuring reliability, security, and performance using CI/CD best practices — requiring the same systems-level thinking and operational stability focus central to managing DevOps platforms at scale. I built Infrastructure-as-Code workflows and automated testing frameworks to validate execution patterns, reducing deployment errors and improving scalability, giving me hands-on experience with the kind of IaC practices (Terraform, Ansible, Chef) this role requires. To keep these systems production-ready, I implemented comprehensive observability and monitoring using structured logging, tracing, and performance metrics, reducing latency by 60% — directly mirroring the reliability, performance, and debugging responsibilities outlined in the job description. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis handling file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO, demonstrating scalability and reliability in multi-cloud environments. I contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform using React, Spring Boot, and AWS, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications with version control, peer review, and automated testing in Agile SDLC — the same collaborative engineering practices this team values. I also developed AWS Step Functions workflows for long-running data import jobs, implementing reliability patterns to prevent Lambda timeouts, and administered relational databases (PostgreSQL, SQL Server) for production systems, optimizing queries, managing backups, implementing security controls, and ensuring performance — giving me the database administration experience, especially with SQL Server, that is highly desirable for this role. Together, these roles have prepared me to manage enterprise-level DevOps tools, databases, and AWS services and contribute meaningfully to ensuring that Infinite Campus provides DevOps platforms that are reliable, scalable, usable, and secure.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in large-scale infrastructure management, system administration, and technical collaboration — skills that translate directly into the engineering discipline and high-performance team culture this role demands. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I managed large-scale engineering infrastructure on an HPC cluster, orchestrating GPU-accelerated training workflows using CUDA and PyTorch with automated deployment. I was responsible for the full infrastructure lifecycle — from resource provisioning and job scheduling to deployment optimization and security controls for production model serving — ensuring both performance and reliability in an enterprise environment. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming, system administration, and AI Agents for 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly, demonstrating the strong problem-solving skills and ability to work independently while also being a strong team player who thrives in a highly collaborative environment — exactly what this role requires. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor, debugs with precision, and communicates with clarity, all of which I would bring to the Platform Engineering team at Infinite Campus.

I have always been passionate about transforming education through technology and promoting stakeholder collaboration, and I envision myself contributing my talent to furthering Infinite Campus's mission of Transforming K12 Education®. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

